betterquesting:10.desc:8: The very first tier, tier zero. This chapter will introduce you to the basic mechanics of this modpack. Mods covered: Vanilla, Pam's Harvestcraft.
GT++ adds new functionality to GT, including high speed multiblocks.
Warp included.
Uhh... hi? You really aren't supposed to be here, you know? We're still, you know, making this tier, right?
If there's a way to generate EU, it'll be on this tab, so check back after a new milestone to see if anything became available.
A questline about oil refining, oil byproducts, and oil based power generation.
A treatise on magical herbology and Botania
This tier is all about the platline, and making the assembly line. They're both super hard , but necessary. This is probably where most people drop out. Good luck!
Tired of torches everywhere making your base look like a loser built it? Make your base look like a winner with these quests.

Congratulations, you've completed the platline, assline, CAL, §oand§r fusion reactor and made it to the Zero Point Module tier. You're well into the late game now, but there's still a lot of stuff to do. Good luck!
Finally some real power to work with. This tier is all about getting to the moon to gather more rare resources to build even more advanced machines.
Magic lies beyond. Great achievements, but also a lot of work. I shall be your guide. Follow my instructions, and you shall become a great wizard, like me.
When regular magic just won't cover it, pay demons to do it for you! The cost might scare some people... But no risk no fun!

Ultimate Voltage! This is the final tier in normal GregTech, but here in GregTech: New Horizons, we pierce the heavens to go beyond the limit! You have done something that only a few players are capable of doing. Welcome to the Endgame!
A guide to help you start Galacticraft to reach the Moon and beyond

The first "voltage" tier of this pack. Things should be a little easier with some of the machines you can now make, and almost every type of machine is now available, try not to be overwhelmed. You can get away with using LV machines for automating processing of things like polyethylene or electrolyzing water the whole game, so consider setting that up when you need it.
A non-tiered quest set that is meant as an in game, quest based tutorial and guide to bees. Since they are a really helpful tool to advance forward.
A series of questlines dedicated to nuclear fission and fusion, both for power and useful items.
Treasure of lands far beyond the vast sea of the Void and very angry rune spiders await you!
This tab continues the basics until you make your first steam machine, and are ready for the real GT stuff
Automated Farms, tree breeding, and more.....
Ultimate (magical) POWER!!!
Catch it, grow it, eat it!
These quests will give you something to use your Coins on. So come on in and and buy some useful or fancy stuff.
You can find ways to store EU here and ways to transform between voltages.

If you have made it this far, you should walk with your head held high - you are at the start of the lategame. Endgame is still a long road ahead of you, but you are now an expert at GTNH and most of the mods it comes with. Congrats, and be proud of yourself.

Once you're done being proud, start making CALs for better circuits, and work towards making endgame power with the Fusion Reactor, you'll need it.
Steve's Carts and ProjectRed automation, for your auto-farming and auto-crafting needs, lag included!
SFM and OC have your back for assline automation! And automating other stuff too complex for AE2, like infusion or blood altars. You can do a lot of cool stuff with OC, feel free to give it a try.
This world is full of nasty things. Time to kill some and improve your reputation.
Welcome to EV! You have successfully gone to the moon and processed Titanium. You are now getting extreme levels of energy. In this tier you will unlock Nuclear energy, and Applied Energistics 2.
This set is a global tracker for multiblock structure goals. As you can build several parts of many multiblocks way earlier than the respective tier. Check back often.
Collection of endgame objectives, good luck and thanks for playing so far.

AE2 focuses on creating a compact, easily accessible, considerably extendible storage system called an ME Network. You can use it to autocraft items as well, and if you want to finish the pack, you will.

Your second voltage tier. Don't mix different voltage levels, or you'll have a fancy new crater. Start thinking about how to expand your base. 

BTW, for OCing purposes, this counts as tier 2, ULV doesn't count.
Questline about powergen that comes from plants and trees.
Granny Weatherwax would approve.
All our collected wisdom, in one convenient place. Many Greggers died to bring you this knowledge.
Steam to electricity (EU) is the progression of this tab. Most of the machines you make in this tier you'll use the whole game, if in an upgraded form.
Breeding Bees for Better Bling (experimental, may cause honey leakage)
Do you know which wand focus is useful and which not? Also, some EMT stuff.
Upgrade your loot bags!
In order to not die constantly, you'll need weapons, armor and transportation. There's also utility stuff like minecarts/trains, adventure backpacks and jetpacks.
